wikipedia_page.main: Robert Page Sewell (3 September 1866 – 7 February 1901) was an English first-class cricketer active 1884–95 who played for Kent. He was born in Maldon and died in Surbiton.

response: * Robert Sewell (historian) (1845–1925), worked in the civil service of the Madras Presidency
* Robert Sewell (lawyer) (1751–1828), Attorney General of Jamaica and member of the Parliament of Great Britain
